HEADWORD: Compluvium
<hw>Com*plu"vi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A space left unroofed over the court of a Roman
dwelling, through which the rain fell into the <xex>impluvium</xex> or
cistern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

